Document: VisualShaderNodeFaceForward
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodefaceforward.rst
Summary: This class implements the faceforward function for orienting vectors in shaders.

This class translates to faceforward(N, I, Nref) in the shader language. The function takes three vector parameters: N (the vector to orient), I (the incident vector), and Nref (the reference vector). If the dot product of I and Nref is less than zero, the return value is N. Otherwise, -N is returned. The operation ensures the vector N is oriented in the same direction as the reference vector Nref relative to the incident vector I.